</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="198" pageNumber="802" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="198.[2059,2651,295,723]" lastBlockId="198.[1444,2648,729,1195]" pageId="198" pageNumber="802">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2059,2344,611,645]" pageId="198" pageNumber="802">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 98-115 mm, tail 111-141 mm, ear 15-19 mm, hindfoot 21-23 mm; weight 25-36 g. Fur of Baer’s Wood Mouse is soft and dense, medium brown above and pure white below. Tail is long (c.122% of head-body length). Ears and eyes are large relative to head. Fifth digit on hindfoot is opposable and almost as long as second to fourth digits. Females have three pairs of nipples. Incisors are orthodont.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
